data.meta_description: Feb 10, 2013 - Marie Prevost (November 8, 1898 â€“ January 21, 1937) was a Canadian-born film actress. During her twenty-year career, she made 121 silent and talking pictures.  She was discovered by Mack Sennett who signed her to contract and made her one of his "Bathing Beauties" in the late 1910s..  She appeared in dozens of Sennett's short comedy films before moving on to feature length films for Universal. See more ideas about marie prevost, prevost, bathing beauties.
